In Hawaii, Queensland- maple seeds are sown as soon as they are collected, at a rate of 150 to 200/m2 (14 to 18/ft2) and at a sowing depth of 0.6 to 1.2 cm (1/4 to 1/2 in). Young seedlings should be provided overhead shade for about the first 2 months. Seedlings may be outplanted as 1+0 seedlings (Wick 1974).
